    "content": "If you're not sure where a Dub link will take you, you can check its destination before clicking on it by adding a `+` sign to the end of the short link.\n\nFor example, if you want to check the destination of the short link `dub.sh/github`, you can type `dub.sh/github+` into your browser's address bar and press `Enter`.\n\n<Image\n  alt=\"Inspect a Dub link's destination\"\n  src=\"https://d2vwwcvoksz7ty.cloudfront.net/changelog/link-inspector.png\"\n  width={1607}\n  height={945}\n/>\n\nThis will take you to a page that shows you the destination URL of the short link, as well as the respective social media preview for the URL.\n\n## Reporting a malicious link\n\nIf you suspect that a Dub link is malicious, you can report it by clicking on the `🚩` button on the link inspector page.\n\n<Image\n  alt=\"Reporting a malicious link on Dub\"\n  src=\"https://d2vwwcvoksz7ty.cloudfront.net/help/report-link.png\"\n  width={2226}\n  height={1406}\n/>\n\nThis will open up a form where you can provide more information about the malicious link.\n\n<Image\n  alt=\"Reporting a malicious link on Dub\"\n  src=\"https://d2vwwcvoksz7ty.cloudfront.net/help/report-link-form.png\"\n  width={2484}\n  height={1592}\n/>\n\nWe take these reports very seriously and will review and take appropriate action as soon as possible.\n\nLearn more about the types of links that are against our [Terms of Service](/terms#3-fair-use).",
    "title": "How can I check a Dub link's destination before clicking on it?",
    "updatedAt": "2023-08-27",
    "summary": "Learn how to check a Dub link's destination to make sure it's safe to click on.",
