    "content": "If you're using a domain on Cloudflare for your Dub project, you might need to configure a few extra steps to make sure that your domain works properly.\n\n<Prerequisites>\n  If you haven't already, you'll need to add your domain to your Dub project.\n  You can learn how to do that [here](how-to-add-custom-domain).\n</Prerequisites>\n\n## Using Cloudflare's Proxy\n\nIf you're using Cloudflare's proxy for your custom domain, you'll need to make sure that your SSL/TLS encryption mode is set to \"Full\" on Cloudflare.\n\n<Image\n  alt=\"Using Cloudflare's proxy for your custom domain\"\n  src=\"https://d2vwwcvoksz7ty.cloudfront.net/help/cloudflare-with-proxy.png\"\n  width={1304}\n  height={372}\n/>\n\nYou can do that by following these steps:\n\n1. Go to your Cloudflare dashboard and select your domain.\n2. Click on the **SSL/TLS** tab on the sidebar menu.\n3. Under **Overview**, select the **Full** option.\n\n<Image\n  alt={`SSL/TLS encryption mode needs to be set to \"Full\" on Cloudflare`}\n  src=\"https://d2vwwcvoksz7ty.cloudfront.net/help/cloudflare-domain-full.png\"\n  width={1822}\n  height={1088}\n/>\n\nThis will make sure that the traffic to your domain is always encrypted between Cloudflare and Dub. You can learn more about Cloudflare's SSL/TLS encryption modes [here](https://developers.cloudflare.com/ssl/origin-configuration/ssl-modes/).\n\n## Using Cloudflare's DNS only (without proxy)\n\nIf you're only using Cloudflare's DNS for your custom domain, all you need to do is [set your domain's DNS records](how-to-add-custom-domain#step-2-configure-your-domain) to point to Dub's servers and make sure that you're using the **DNS only** option on Cloudflare.\n\n<Image\n  alt={`Set your domain's Proxy status to \"DNS only\" on Cloudflare (greyed out cloud icon)`}\n  src=\"https://d2vwwcvoksz7ty.cloudfront.net/help/cloudflare-without-proxy.png\"\n  width={1304}\n  height={372}\n/>\n\nThis will make sure that the traffic to your domain is _not proxied through Cloudflare_ and is sent directly to Dub. You can learn more about Cloudflare's proxy options [here](https://support.cloudflare.com/hc/en-us/articles/200169626-Identifying-network-ports-compatible-with-Cloudflare-s-proxy).",
